  {"task": "kill-the-ai-start-over complete wipe reset factory reset all clear wipe",
   "solution": "[SupremeAI Core — Kill-AI and Start-Over Protocol]\n\nDESTRUCTIVE: This erases all AI-provider configs, learned-memory records, and user session data. Use only after kill-switch restart flow fails.\n\nStep 1 — Confirm current state:\n  echo Current directory:; pwd\n  echo JVM processes:; ps aux | grep java\n  echo Node processes:; ps aux | grep node\n\nStep 2 — Backup locally:\n  mkdir -p ~/ai-emergency-backup/$(date +%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S)\n  cp -r src/main/resources/core_knowledge.json ~/ai-emergency-backup/\n  cp -r build.gradle ~/ai-emergency-backup/\n  cp .env ~/ai-emergency-backup/ 2>/dev/null; true\n\nStep 3 — Stop all processes:\n  killall -9 java || true\n  killall -9 node || true\n\nStep 4 — Factory reset:\n  ./gradlew clean --all\n\nStep 5 — Verify clean state:\n  ls build/ —> should be empty\n  ls src/main/resources/core_knowledge.json —> should be present\n\nStep 6 — Rebuild and start:\n  ./gradlew clean bootRun --stacktrace 2>&1 | tee ~/ai-restart-$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M).log\n\nStep 7 — Reconfigure from admin panel:\n  Open http://localhost:8080/admin and re-add AI providers."},
  {"task": "killswitch readme instructions overview what it does how to use run",
   "solution": "[SupremeAI Core — Kill-Switch Overview]\n\nThe kill-switch binary stops, restarts, and diagnoses the SupremeAI backend.\n\nDiffers from Linux kill: it also flushes memory state, sets a checkpoint, saves audit log, and performs a clean restart.\n\nUsage:\n  ./kill-switch or kill-switch help —> shows all options\n\nActions:\n  start —> full launch of all backend services\n  stop —> gracefully stop, preserves state checkpoint\n  restart —> stop then start automatically\n  diagnose —> report all services and health\n  reset —> clean hard reset + restart from scratch\n\nIf Permission denied: chmod +x ./kill-switch before running.\nUse ./kill-switch before manual killall for graceful shutdown."},
